WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.400 --> 00:00:02.640
Wow, that was fast.

00:00:03.200 --> 00:00:05.013
Well, good evening everybody.

00:00:05.013 --> 00:00:07.840
Thank you for joining us tonight.

00:00:08.320 --> 00:00:12.180
I don't know where Braden wants to go from here.

00:00:12.180 --> 00:00:21.680
I've got my microphone, but I had a really interesting conversation yesterday on the phone.

00:00:24.400 --> 00:00:30.606
Every year, I evaluate where we are, what the Lord has done, and what we could do better.

00:00:30.949 --> 00:00:40.420
Especially now that we're in ministry, I evaluate the intimacy level—checking your thermostat, as I call it.

00:00:40.420 --> 00:00:43.383
Where is your thermostat with God?

00:00:43.383 --> 00:00:44.200
How are things?

00:00:44.200 --> 00:01:06.359
If you were to get your report card or your evaluation at work for how you did for the year—your review for the year—and the boss comes in and says, 'Well, you could have done this better, or you did this really well, and your progress report was pretty good, so we'll give you a raise or keep you where you are.

00:01:06.359 --> 00:01:12.240
' I go over things with the Father like that all the time at the end of the year.

00:01:13.640 --> 00:01:22.400
I always evaluate and write things down because I don't want to be where I am at this time next year.

00:01:22.604 --> 00:01:25.387
I look and see if I made any progress spiritually.

00:01:27.246 --> 00:01:46.979
After I had a really interesting conversation with a mega-minister yesterday—he called and wanted to talk to me—I asked some questions that I normally don't ask, but the Lord told me to ask him because he would have the answers.

00:01:49.510 --> 00:01:59.199
I asked about a lot of mega-prophets and how come they didn't sustain in ministry or why they went home early.

00:02:06.270 --> 00:02:12.151
I asked what happened to some of these prophetic voices that have gone before us.

00:02:13.307 --> 00:02:27.689
He went over the details of why some of these major voices that used to be—that are no more—fell, and why their ministries faltered.

00:02:32.533 --> 00:02:34.114
He knew a lot of the answers.

00:02:34.468 --> 00:02:39.760
As we were talking, it really bothered me.

00:02:42.239 --> 00:02:43.599
One person was messed up with homosexuality.

00:02:43.871 --> 00:02:46.599
One was messing around with golden idols.

00:03:00.926 --> 00:03:03.760
There were so many different things.

00:03:04.423 --> 00:03:10.106
As I heard it all, I paused.

00:03:10.675 --> 00:03:19.360
They all started out really good with great intentions and great intimacy with the Father.

00:03:19.360 --> 00:03:22.239
You don't get there without intimacy.

00:03:22.239 --> 00:03:23.960
But what went wrong?

00:03:24.390 --> 00:03:37.990
I'm not going to reveal these men's names, but as I was thinking about people I had looked up to and admired, you see the slow fade after year after year of ministry.

00:03:43.236 --> 00:03:45.396
I didn't get the answer right off.

00:03:45.396 --> 00:03:52.880
I was praying all last night and seeking the Lord because of the things He's showing me.

00:04:00.453 --> 00:04:11.439
As you're checking your thermostat of where you are with the Father, you have to ask, 'How is my relationship with God?

00:04:11.439 --> 00:04:20.160
' I don't ever want to be arrogant and say, 'That will never happen to me,' because these people, in my opinion, were the best over the years.

00:04:21.804 --> 00:04:25.973
How do you stay on the right road?

00:04:25.973 --> 00:04:27.840
How do you self-evaluate?

00:04:38.462 --> 00:04:43.040
I woke up this morning and the Lord spoke to me in my sleep.

00:04:43.616 --> 00:04:55.360
He said, 'Intimacy is what gets you there with Me, and intimacy is what will keep you there.

00:04:55.360 --> 00:05:06.319
' So many times, these ministers start with healings, demonstrations, and manifestations, but they lose the intimacy with the Father.

00:05:06.319 --> 00:05:09.520
The gift is separate from intimacy.

00:05:09.520 --> 00:05:17.520
Intimacy is how you got the gift, but it's not how you sustain it.

00:05:19.431 --> 00:05:34.548
Over time, you get so caught up—because it's trying to happen to me—with the pulling on the gift that you believe walking underneath that mantle is intimacy for the day.

00:05:35.919 --> 00:05:48.560
You're so busy with all the people pulling on you that you don't separate yourself to have the intimacy that got the gift in the first place.

00:05:58.080 --> 00:06:01.600
It becomes robotic.

00:06:01.920 --> 00:06:06.000
The Lord said, 'Brandon, it's a slow fade.

00:06:06.000 --> 00:06:20.960
Many of the ministers you were told about yesterday started out just like you—on fire and effective.

00:06:20.960 --> 00:06:26.639
But the gift and callings of God are without repentance.

00:06:26.639 --> 00:06:37.600
' You can operate in a gift while there is stuff going on in your personal life because the gift is without repentance.

00:06:37.600 --> 00:06:46.479
You qualify for it, but if you cut yourself off the vine, you don't die instantaneously.

00:06:57.440 --> 00:07:02.960
Intimacy keeps you on the vine.

00:07:03.760 --> 00:07:15.680
You cannot let intimacy with the Father die, or eventually, your ministry will be short-lived.

00:07:19.577 --> 00:07:23.775
You cannot rely just on the experience of healings and demonstrations.

00:07:26.080 --> 00:07:37.737
I always tell you that covering comes on me and I can feel it when I'm praying, but the Lord was warning me: just because you have that impartation at that time doesn't mean you're walking in intimacy with Me.

00:07:38.400 --> 00:07:40.826
You have to check your spiritual thermostat.

00:07:40.826 --> 00:07:43.759
They are two different things.

00:07:55.690 --> 00:08:00.240
He's been talking to me about evaluating your progress report.

00:08:09.660 --> 00:08:13.440
I'm real open about things, and I learn as I go.

00:08:17.988 --> 00:08:23.560
Some of the elders who went before us, like Jack Coe, were warned about their weight.

00:08:26.311 --> 00:08:31.440
He was in his 30s when he passed away.

00:08:31.440 --> 00:08:42.800
What a tragic thing for somebody who walked in so much creative miracles to only have a ministry last until their 30s.

00:08:54.009 --> 00:08:54.360
This is so taxing, with so much demand.

00:09:11.636 --> 00:09:11.920
If you keep going down the road—because some people were committing adultery or were homosexual—the Lord warned them, 'If you keep going down this road, you're going to hell.

00:09:11.920 --> 00:09:19.529
' The word of the Lord came up so strong about this stuff that it shook me.

00:09:24.760 --> 00:09:27.485
I even knew a man personally who was messing around on his wife for two years prior to getting caught.

00:09:33.199 --> 00:09:33.679
The only reason he got caught was a text message.

00:09:33.679 --> 00:09:35.660
People ask how he kept preaching.

00:09:35.660 --> 00:09:38.524
He said the word is truth regardless.

00:09:38.524 --> 00:09:40.840
So I'm just preaching the word.

00:09:40.840 --> 00:09:50.331
It's okay; I knew that if I could just keep preaching the word, it didn't matter about my personal life because the word always stands by itself.

00:10:06.659 --> 00:10:09.406
I believe that was it, wasn't it?

00:10:09.406 --> 00:10:14.302
And I was just thinking that is such a dangerous place to be.

00:10:14.302 --> 00:10:28.640
But just going over your year for 2025 and going into 2026 and looking at what God has for you so that you take what you did well into the year and strip off the bad things.

00:10:28.640 --> 00:10:34.320
And the Lord told me, 'Brandon, I've warned and warned my people.

00:10:34.320 --> 00:10:46.530
' It keeps stirring up inside of me, what the Lord told me to say about 2026 and 1 Corinthians 5:5.

00:10:46.530 --> 00:10:50.782
As I lay there this morning and listened to the Father, I said, 'God, help me.

00:10:50.782 --> 00:10:54.320
Search me, know me, create in me a clean heart.

00:10:54.320 --> 00:10:56.000
Strip all this stuff off.

00:10:56.000 --> 00:11:03.040
Whatever it takes, intimacy with Me is more important than anything else.

00:11:03.040 --> 00:11:08.760
Who cares if the platform pulls you away from the Father?

00:11:08.760 --> 00:11:16.800
If you're so distracted with the platform, then it's time to prune it.

00:11:16.800 --> 00:11:18.930
Does that make sense?

00:11:18.930 --> 00:11:19.619
He's first.

00:11:22.891 --> 00:11:28.914
Intimacy is everything to have a relationship—the fellowship that got you there in the first place—to sustain it.

00:11:28.914 --> 00:11:32.103
That's where dryness comes in.

00:11:32.103 --> 00:11:34.079
There's so much dryness.

00:11:34.079 --> 00:11:43.120
I see pastors teaching out of their dryness and there's no good word.

00:11:55.840 --> 00:11:56.080
I even talked to one man and he said, 'It's interesting.

00:12:02.959 --> 00:12:04.435
I can go into a service and they're still preaching on something that they were preaching 30 years ago.

00:12:04.435 --> 00:12:11.946
Thirty years later, they don't have any new wine or new wineskins, continually preaching the same thing.

00:12:11.946 --> 00:12:24.700
' You get to the point where you ask, 'Do you not have any fresh Rhema from God?

00:12:24.700 --> 00:12:34.160
' Now, I know Brother Hagin taught Mark 11:23-24, but there was an anointing on it when he preached it.

00:12:44.720 --> 00:12:48.296
You could feel the tangible presence of God when he taught that.

00:12:48.296 --> 00:12:51.874
So obviously, in those cases, it was meant for him to preach.

00:12:51.874 --> 00:12:59.760
Now, for some of these other people, it's like going into the Mojave Desert and wondering, 'Why am I even here?

00:12:59.760 --> 00:13:11.760
' It's interesting when you talk to people who have been through the trenches, like the person I talked to yesterday and another one of my mentors.

00:13:13.751 --> 00:13:16.560
It's been interesting, the people who have called.

00:13:17.976 --> 00:13:26.079
You get to meditate on these things and walk away thinking, 'I don't want to say I'll never do that.

00:13:26.079 --> 00:13:32.194
' I always want to self-evaluate and be humble about it.

00:13:32.525 --> 00:13:35.211
I'm not saying I'm better than them; heavens, no.

00:13:35.211 --> 00:13:39.519
For some of these people, I couldn't even tie their shoelaces.

00:13:39.519 --> 00:13:47.577
But if you don't self-evaluate your relationship and look at your thermostat with God, you'll drift off easily.

00:13:48.285 --> 00:13:58.959
Just because you have a call and there's a mantle or an impartation on that call doesn't mean that your intimacy level is good.

00:13:58.959 --> 00:14:04.530
You must self-evaluate all the time and say, 'Father, how are you and I?

00:14:04.530 --> 00:14:05.851
Not the ministry.

00:14:05.851 --> 00:14:08.480
How am I with you?

00:14:08.480 --> 00:14:09.800
How are things going?

00:14:09.800 --> 00:14:11.120
Am I doing okay?

00:14:11.120 --> 00:14:13.519
Am I pleasing to you?

00:14:13.519 --> 00:14:18.853
' After I sat and wept on the floor, He gave me a word.

00:14:19.120 --> 00:14:20.440
That word was intimacy.

00:14:20.440 --> 00:14:28.320
It was private for me, but I'm very thankful for where I am with my Father.

00:14:28.320 --> 00:14:30.800
Yes, there are things you can work on.

00:14:31.360 --> 00:14:38.624
Ultimately, if you cut yourself from the vine, you don't instantaneously dry up and die.

00:14:38.920 --> 00:14:42.160
It's a slow fade.

00:14:47.689 --> 00:14:47.911
You are dying instantaneously, but the branch always has life for a little bit.

00:14:47.911 --> 00:14:52.480
You can even cut it and see green underneath the bark.

00:14:52.480 --> 00:15:04.959
The leaves start to wither first, the fruit fades, and all of a sudden, what was once alive becomes dead because He's the true source.

00:15:05.496 --> 00:15:12.560
I realized as I listened that I don't want to be a statistic in ministry.

00:15:13.496 --> 00:15:21.190
So as I focus on what could be done better in 2026, I want the capacity to reach the lost to increase.

00:15:21.190 --> 00:15:27.479
The capacity for healing must increase—not just physical healing, but mental and emotional healing.

00:15:27.479 --> 00:15:35.109
There are so many people on our email list dealing with mental drama.

00:15:43.767 --> 00:15:55.560
I try to be a place of refreshing for all people to come and drink from, so that when they are here, they get a fresh touch from the Holy Ghost.

00:15:55.940 --> 00:16:09.611
The only way you can give—'Silver and gold have I none, but such as I have give I thee: In the name of Jesus Christ of Nazareth rise up and walk'—is through intimacy.

00:16:09.611 --> 00:16:11.866
They had been with Jesus.

00:16:11.866 --> 00:16:17.074
They were unlearned, uneducated men who had been with Jesus.

00:16:17.074 --> 00:16:18.560
That's what the Bible says.

00:16:19.813 --> 00:16:24.926
The world marveled because they had been with Jesus.

00:16:25.360 --> 00:16:31.990
It's not just being with Him once; it's being with Him continually, sitting at His feet.

00:16:31.990 --> 00:16:36.719
It's the intimacy with the Father that says, 'Jesus, I'm here.

00:16:36.719 --> 00:16:39.380
I need You to change me and take me from glory to glory.

00:16:39.380 --> 00:16:50.728
' In Diana's and my case, we practice what we preach when we say we walk in love—sowing even when you don't want to sow, giving and being where God tells you to be.

00:16:50.959 --> 00:16:53.348
It's interesting because we laugh about things.

00:16:53.897 --> 00:16:59.960
We always say Joyce Meyer talks about how in the kingdom of God, a lot of things are backwards.

00:17:06.364 --> 00:17:06.595
When people treat you badly, you don't go after them or be mean; you walk in love.

00:17:07.520 --> 00:17:11.760
When you sow, you give your money away to believe God for extra.

00:17:24.400 --> 00:17:24.720
Everything seems awkward, upside down, and inside out.

00:17:24.720 --> 00:17:27.088
We love Joyce Meyer, don't we?

00:17:27.088 --> 00:17:27.749
Everything goes against your flesh.

00:17:27.749 --> 00:17:34.596
When you think, 'Lord, are You going to release me from this church to move on because of this and that?

00:17:34.596 --> 00:17:43.449
' and the Lord says, 'No, I want you to stay,' and you keep working things out, it makes your flesh scream.

00:17:43.449 --> 00:17:48.880
If your flesh isn't screaming, you aren't growing spiritually.

00:17:48.880 --> 00:17:50.430
You need to know this.

00:17:50.430 --> 00:18:02.160
When He says to clean toilets for years, do it with a good heart—without grumbling and complaining.

00:18:02.160 --> 00:18:05.439
Live in a shotgun house for 20 years.

00:18:05.439 --> 00:18:09.919
Do what I've asked without grumbling and complaining.

00:18:09.919 --> 00:18:18.080
Do all that you do, in word and deed, to the glory of God, and He'll release you.

00:18:18.080 --> 00:18:23.760
Do it with a joyful heart.

00:18:23.760 --> 00:18:29.880
The willing and obedient will eat the good of the land, not the grudging.

00:18:29.880 --> 00:18:34.907
There are so many times the Lord tells Diana and me to do something against our flesh.

00:18:34.907 --> 00:18:37.039
He says, 'I want you to sow this.

00:18:37.039 --> 00:18:39.333
' I think, 'Are you kidding me?

00:18:39.333 --> 00:18:45.000
' But then I say, 'Okay, I'll do it.

00:18:45.000 --> 00:18:52.460
' But I can't do it with a grudging heart; I have to do it with joy.

00:18:52.460 --> 00:18:54.400
'I love a cheerful giver, Brandon.

00:18:54.400 --> 00:18:58.080
' So I do it with a cheerful attitude and walk in love.

00:19:01.480 --> 00:19:01.840
This happens to me all the time.

00:19:06.232 --> 00:19:07.973
The Lord says, 'This is molding you.

00:19:07.973 --> 00:19:17.360
If you do what I tell you, you'll go to the next level.

00:19:17.360 --> 00:19:19.964
I'm watching your heart.

00:19:19.964 --> 00:19:25.050
' In a vision, I saw a path of white; it was beautiful but skinny, with no edges.

00:19:25.050 --> 00:19:28.100
As far as the eye could see, it was a dimension.

00:19:30.1000 --> 00:19:33.129
I pulled out of it because it freaked me out.

00:19:33.502 --> 00:19:37.789
I had to meditate on it because the Lord was dealing with me.

00:19:40.919 --> 00:19:43.631
I saw the nose.

00:19:43.631 --> 00:19:49.017
I saw a cheek, and I saw the side of a mouth.

00:19:49.531 --> 00:19:55.983
His face was right on the edge of the path, but his eye was all I could see.

00:19:56.687 --> 00:20:01.690
I didn't say this, but he spoke to me in an audible voice in my house.

00:20:01.690 --> 00:20:03.609
That's why it freaked me out.

00:20:03.609 --> 00:20:04.382
I heard it.

00:20:04.382 --> 00:20:11.350
And he says, 'I'm watching you.

00:20:11.360 --> 00:20:11.691
I'm watching you.

00:20:11.691 --> 00:20:18.000
' And that's why I started singing His Eye Is on the Sparrow, for I know he watches me.

00:20:18.000 --> 00:20:24.320
That's why I sang that song because he said to me, 'I'm watching you, Brandon.

00:20:24.320 --> 00:20:29.146
I'm watching you and how you make these decisions and these choices.

00:20:29.146 --> 00:20:33.600
Do you qualify to go to the next level?

00:20:33.600 --> 00:20:37.280
Do you qualify to get more?

00:20:37.280 --> 00:20:39.333
I have more in store in 2026.

00:20:39.333 --> 00:20:42.114
I have more in store in the days ahead.

00:20:42.114 --> 00:20:45.200
' But do you qualify for it?

00:20:45.200 --> 00:20:48.400
What qualifies you?

00:20:48.400 --> 00:20:50.240
Obedience.

00:20:50.240 --> 00:20:53.280
Listening whenever your flesh screams.

00:20:53.280 --> 00:21:00.000
Will you qualify, ladies and gentlemen, for what God has for you by obedience?

00:21:00.000 --> 00:21:01.533
Obedience is better than sacrifice.

00:21:01.533 --> 00:21:04.640
And it's not always easy when he tells you...

00:21:04.640 --> 00:21:09.189
when people call and say, 'I got another call yesterday to go to the White House.

00:21:09.189 --> 00:21:12.080
' This is the fourth time.

00:21:12.400 --> 00:21:17.360
To go to the White House, fourth time.

00:21:17.360 --> 00:21:20.240
'No, don't go.

00:21:20.240 --> 00:21:21.600
Not yet.

00:21:21.600 --> 00:21:23.022
' 'Well, you need to give me an answer.

00:21:23.022 --> 00:21:24.986
' I could have been there today at the White House.

00:21:27.720 --> 00:21:34.811
It could have been very interesting to meet Jentezen Franklin and Paula White again and another man.

00:21:34.811 --> 00:21:35.188
These people...

00:21:35.188 --> 00:21:39.327
I always butcher his name, that's why I don't try to say it.

00:21:39.327 --> 00:21:43.360
It's his Spanish name, a pastor from Miami.

00:21:43.360 --> 00:21:45.919
That's what I say.

00:21:45.919 --> 00:21:49.920
Sorry, I know he's probably watching; I don't mean to be rude.

00:21:50.320 --> 00:22:10.559
It's just I'm not real good with names sometimes, but all the opportunities that come across your path, you're so thankful for what God opens the door maybe, but at the same time, I want to make sure I don't do things without hearing him.

00:22:10.559 --> 00:22:17.120
So I say, I was taught by another prophetic voice: go low, go slow.

00:22:19.119 --> 00:22:20.354
Don't do anything quick.

00:22:20.354 --> 00:22:22.960
If it needs a quick answer, tell them no.

00:22:23.340 --> 00:22:26.507
Go low, go slow inside.

00:22:28.551 --> 00:22:36.000
And that's what we do.

00:22:36.000 --> 00:22:36.818
It's very...

00:22:36.818 --> 00:22:42.480
and I learned that's what keeps you on balance.

00:22:42.480 --> 00:22:44.320
Do you want to read what the Lord said?

00:22:44.320 --> 00:22:47.653
Because he said it a lot better when you get it on recording.

00:22:47.653 --> 00:22:48.400
'Love, Diana.

00:22:48.400 --> 00:22:49.939
' 'Oh, I thought you said it perfect.

00:22:49.939 --> 00:22:51.039
You want me to still read it?

00:22:51.039 --> 00:22:51.599
' 'No.

00:22:51.599 --> 00:22:52.159
Did I say it perfect?

00:22:52.159 --> 00:22:53.280
' 'You said it beautiful.

00:22:53.280 --> 00:22:54.140
' Okay, love.

00:22:54.140 --> 00:23:10.480
I just want to make sure because I want to communicate it where people get this, because if you don't listen to what I'm telling you, I truly believe with all my heart that people won't make it in ministry, just like we've seen.

00:23:10.480 --> 00:23:30.869
And I keep trying to go and I want so bad for longevity, but not just longevity where you see mega-ministers with big houses, big cars, big planes, runways, whatever, with hundreds of millions in the bank, whatever TV program.

00:23:31.511 --> 00:23:36.100
Listen, folks, I'm just into him.

00:23:36.100 --> 00:23:39.143
The byproduct of following him is blessing.

00:23:39.143 --> 00:23:40.480
I get that.

00:23:40.480 --> 00:23:55.360
But where I'm at right now is I want that anointing so strong that whenever people see it, they see Jesus in me and they say, 'Brandon, what must I do to be saved?

00:23:55.360 --> 00:23:58.640
What must I do to be saved?

00:23:58.640 --> 00:24:13.387
' I am so broken that when my shadow passes by, the power of God radiates out of me so strong that they get healed by the Holy Ghost because the glory of the Lord is inside of me.

00:24:13.387 --> 00:24:19.200
Silver and gold have I none, but such as I have give I thee.

00:24:19.200 --> 00:24:24.777
I think about them all the time—the disciples—and they walked...

00:24:24.777 --> 00:24:27.919
they had been with Jesus.

00:24:27.919 --> 00:24:42.240
What does it take to stay with Jesus in these modern days with all these distractions, with all the social media and all these things, and you've got to get money and you've got to raise your kids and go to church?

00:24:42.240 --> 00:24:47.280
You've got all these things and all these voices, and I just keep the main thing the main thing.

00:24:47.880 --> 00:24:57.919
And it's like my friend Billy says—call him my mentor now, my spiritual father: 'Go vertical, Brandon.

00:24:57.919 --> 00:25:01.840
You must stay vertical and keep humble.

00:25:01.840 --> 00:25:08.415
' The longevity, even in your ministry, is to maintain humility in these last days.

00:25:08.911 --> 00:25:16.720
I always listen to him; maintain humility.

00:25:16.720 --> 00:25:23.980
There's so much arrogance and so much pride in people, and God resists the proud.

00:25:23.980 --> 00:25:32.320
He gives grace to the humble and in due time, he said he would exalt you.

00:25:32.320 --> 00:25:33.460
So, in humility...

